# DialogueDemoSystem  (sbx)

## Purpose
Drives the typewriter dialogue demo. Returns early until SandboxConfigSingletonComponent is present,
then lazily creates DialogueDemoSingletonComponent (seeded with a default line and reveal speed). Each
ready frame it renders an ImGui "Dialogue" panel — a multi-line text field, a chars/sec slider, and a
Replay button — guarded so it is skipped in the test build (no ImGui context). Independent of ImGui,
it detects when the edited line changed (restarting the reveal from the first character), advances the
reveal by chars/sec × frame time (clamped to the line length), finds the fixed-size word-wrapped
dialogue text element by UUID, and emits a UIUpdateTextRevealOneFrameComponent carrying the current
line and visible-character count. The engine UIControlSystem applies it, so the line types itself out
in the nine-slice panel and replays whenever the text is edited.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| SandboxConfigSingletonComponent | read | Dialogue text element id; guard |
| BaseComponent | read | Locates the dialogue text element by UUID |
| DialogueDemoSingletonComponent | write | Edited line, last-applied line (change detection), reveal progress + speed |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| DialogueDemoSingletonComponent | write / add (deferred) | Created once with the default line; mutated each frame |
| UIUpdateTextRevealOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | Emitted on the dialogue element each frame: current text + visible-character count |
